<p>“Cultures spring from religions; ultimately the vital force which maintains any culture is its philosophy, its attitude toward the universe; the decay of a religion involves the decay of the culture corresponding to it—we see that most clearly in the breakdown of Christendom today.”—Hilaire Belloc: <em>The Great Heresies</em></p>
<h2 id="eyore">Eyore</h2>
<p>Thursday, 16 January 2020</p>
<p>“Eeyore’s pessimism is the expression of inadequacy and fear. I distinguish the right kind of pessimism, which means simply recognizing the deep incompetence of human nature, from the wrong kind, which tells us to stop hoping.”—Roger Scruton, (27 February 1944 – 12 January 2020)</p>
